{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/TheTurnPipeline"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"sections":[],"kind":"article","metadata":{"role":"article","title":"The Turn Pipeline","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"Gnusto"}]},"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Essentials","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/AnatomyOfAGame"],"title":"Essentials","generated":true}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Every line the player types runs through the same fixed sequence of stages. This section walks that sequence — which rules fire, in what order, and how one rule can stop the rest — from raw input to committed state."}]},{"text":"From input to command","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"From-input-to-command"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/REPL","isActive":true},{"text":" reads a line and hands it to ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameWorld\/perform(_:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":". The parser first turns the text into a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Command","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" — an ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Intent","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" (the canonical action, like "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Intent\/take","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":") plus the objects, preposition, and direction it resolved."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Parsing can fail: an unknown word, nothing in scope, a verb with no object. "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Parse failures are free."}]},{"type":"text","text":" No rules run, the state is untouched, and the turn counter does not advance — the player just sees a message (“I don’t understand that.” \/ “You can’t see any such thing here.”) and a fresh prompt. Only a successfully parsed command enters the pipeline below."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"The-stages-of-a-turn","level":2,"text":"The stages of a turn"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once a command parses, the engine runs these stages in order. Rules are matched by "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"scope"}]},{"type":"text","text":" (world, the current location, or one of the command’s objects) and by "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"intent"}]},{"type":"text","text":" (a rule with no intents listed matches any)."}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"World ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"before"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/World\/before(_:perform:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" rules, matching the intent."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Location ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"beforeEachTurn"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Location\/beforeEachTurn(perform:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" for the current room, every turn regardless of intent."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Location ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"before"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Location\/before(_:perform:)","isActive":true},{"text":" for the current room.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Item ","type":"text"},{"code":"before","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"text":" — ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item\/before(_:perform:)","isActive":true},{"text":" for the indirect object, then the direct object.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default action"}]},{"text":" — the engine’s built-in behavior for the intent (pick up the item, walk through the exit, describe the thing). This is where the turn actually ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"does","type":"text"}]},{"text":" something if no rule intervened.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Item "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"after"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item\/after(_:perform:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" for the direct object, then the indirect object."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Location "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"after"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Location\/after(_:perform:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" for the current room.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Location ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"afterEachTurn"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Location\/afterEachTurn(perform:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for the room, every turn."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"World ","type":"text"},{"code":"after","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/World\/after(_:perform:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" rules.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Then the turn counter advances by one and the turn commits."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The symmetry is deliberate: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"before"},{"type":"text","text":" rules run outside-in (world, then location, then item) so broad rules get first say; "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"after"},{"type":"text","text":" rules run inside-out. A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"before"},{"type":"text","text":" rule is your chance to "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"change or forbid"}]},{"type":"text","text":" what is about to happen; an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"after"},{"type":"text","text":" rule reacts to what "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"did"}]},{"type":"text","text":" happen."}]},{"text":"Stopping the turn: refuse, reply, and end","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Stopping-the-turn-refuse-reply-and-end"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A rule body is ordinary Swift, but three helpers change the flow of the turn by throwing an interrupt the engine catches:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/refuse(_:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" — “no, you can’t.” Prints the message and skips the default action and every remaining "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"before"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"after"},{"type":"text","text":" rule. Use it in a "},{"code":"before","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" rule to veto an action."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/reply(_:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" — “here’s what happens instead.” Mechanically identical to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"refuse"},{"type":"text","text":", but named for the case where you are "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"handling"}]},{"type":"text","text":" the action yourself rather than forbidding it. This is how a custom verb produces its result."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/end(won:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" — ends the game, won or lost. The engine prints the final score after the turn’s output."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All three return "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Never"},{"text":", so they read naturally in a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"guard"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["cloak.before(.drop, .putOn) {","    guard player.location == cloakroom else {","        try refuse(\"This isn't the best place to leave a smart cloak lying around.\")","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To add output "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"without"}]},{"type":"text","text":" stopping the turn, use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/say(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":". It appends a line to the turn’s output and returns normally, so the default action still runs. A "},{"code":"before","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" rule that only "},{"code":"say","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"s adds flavor; one that "},{"code":"refuse","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"s or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reply"},{"type":"text","text":"s takes over."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"World-time-passes-even-on-a-refusal","level":2,"text":"World time passes even on a refusal"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There is one important asymmetry. When a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"before"},{"type":"text","text":" rule refuses an action, the default action and later "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"before"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"after"},{"type":"text","text":" rules are skipped — but the turn is still a turn. The each-turn tail (stages 8 and 9) still runs, and the move counter still advances."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is what makes timed puzzles work. A lantern burning down, a guard on patrol, or — in Cloak of Darkness — the darkness that penalizes "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"any","type":"text"}]},{"text":" fumbling in the dark bar, all live in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"afterEachTurn"},{"text":" rules, and they tick even on the turns the player wasted trying something forbidden. Each-turn rules run independently: if one throws, the engine catches it and moves on to the next, so one region’s daemon can’t silently kill another’s.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Meta-intents-skip-everything","level":2,"text":"Meta intents skip everything"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A few intents talk to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"game program","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":", not the game world: "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Intent\/score"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Intent\/quit","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Intent\/version","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":". These are "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"meta"}]},{"type":"text","text":" intents. They run no rules at all and do not consume a turn — asking for your score is not an action the world should react to, and it should not advance a timed puzzle. Everything in the numbered list above is gated on the intent not being meta."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Everything-commits-at-once","text":"Everything commits at once"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Throughout the turn, rules and the default action read and write a "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"scratch"}]},{"type":"text","text":" copy of the world state. Nothing is visible outside the turn until it finishes. At the very end, the engine commits that scratch state in one step and returns a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/TurnResult","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" — the text to print, whether the game is now finished, and the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/StatusLine","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" to show."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because all mutation funnels through one committed value, a turn is atomic: the player never observes a half-applied turn, and (in a later release) saving the game is just serializing that value. This is the same single-state design described in "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/AnatomyOfAGame","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"See-also","text":"See also"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/WritingRules","isActive":true}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/AnatomyOfAGame","isActive":true}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/AddingCustomVerbs","isActive":true}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"What happens between the player pressing Return and the next prompt."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gnusto\/theturnpipeline"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto"]]},"references":{"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Intent/version":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Intent\/version","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/intent\/version","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"let","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"version","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Intent","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:6Gnusto6IntentV"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Report the engine version."}],"title":"version"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/World/before(_:perform:)":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/World\/before(_:perform:)","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/world\/before(_:perform:)","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"before","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"Intent","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:6Gnusto6IntentV"},{"text":"..., ","kind":"text"},{"text":"perform","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": () ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Void","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s4Voida"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Rule","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:6Gnusto4RuleV"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Runs before the default action whenever the named intents are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"attempted, anywhere."}],"title":"before(_:perform:)"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/end(won:)":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/end(won:)","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"end(won:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"end"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"won"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Never","preciseIdentifier":"s:s5NeverO"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Ends the game. The engine prints the final score after the turn’s output."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/end(won:)"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Intent":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Intent","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"Intent","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Intent"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A canonical action the player can attempt. Games can mint their own"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Intent(\"ring\")"},{"type":"text","text":") and register verbs and default behavior for them."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/intent","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Intent"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/say(_:)":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/say(_:)","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"say(_:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"say"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"String","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Prints a message as part of the turn’s output."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/say(_:)"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/REPL":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/REPL","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/repl","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"REPL","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"REPL","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The outer loop: prompt → parse → perform → print, until the game ends or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"input runs out. Holds the only "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"await"},{"type":"text","text":" in a Gnusto game."}],"title":"REPL"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Intent/score":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Intent\/score","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/intent\/score","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"let","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"score","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Intent","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:6Gnusto6IntentV"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Report the current score."}],"title":"score"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/AddingCustomVerbs":{"role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/AddingCustomVerbs","type":"topic","kind":"article","title":"Adding Custom Verbs","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Teach the parser words the built-in table doesn’t know."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/addingcustomverbs"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Item/before(_:perform:)":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item\/before(_:perform:)","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/item\/before(_:perform:)","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"before","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"Intent","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:6Gnusto6IntentV"},{"text":"..., ","kind":"text"},{"text":"perform","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": () ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Void","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s4Voida"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Rule","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:6Gnusto4RuleV"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Runs before the default action when the named intents target this item."}],"title":"before(_:perform:)"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/reply(_:)":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/reply(_:)","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"reply(_:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"reply"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"String","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Never","preciseIdentifier":"s:s5NeverO"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Fully handles the current action with a response, skipping the default"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"behavior. Mechanically identical to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"refuse(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" — two names exist so"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"game code reads correctly: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"refuse"},{"type":"text","text":" for “no, you can’t”, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reply"},{"type":"text","text":" for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"“here’s what happens instead”."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/reply(_:)"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Location/after(_:perform:)":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Location\/after(_:perform:)","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/location\/after(_:perform:)","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"after","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"Intent","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:6Gnusto6IntentV"},{"text":"..., ","kind":"text"},{"text":"perform","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": () ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Void","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s4Voida"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Rule","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:6Gnusto4RuleV"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Runs after the default action when the named intents succeed in this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"location."}],"title":"after(_:perform:)"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GettingStarted":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GettingStarted","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/gettingstarted","kind":"article","role":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Build and run your first text adventure, one piece at a time."}],"title":"Getting Started with Gnusto"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/AnatomyOfAGame":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"How a single Swift type becomes a world the engine can run."}],"kind":"article","type":"topic","title":"Anatomy of a Game","role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/anatomyofagame","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/AnatomyOfAGame"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A Swift engine for writing parser-driven interactive fiction — text adventures in the tradition of Zork and Infocom’s ZIL."}],"title":"Gnusto"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Intent/quit":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnu